        <div class="comment-content">
            <p>Whole Foods markets carries strips of dried persimmon for $7.50 for 4oz.  It tastes good just as dried fruit.  I also found many sites by Googling "Dried Persimmon".</p>

<p>The Peoples Pharmacy guide on "Heartburn/Digestion" offers a lot of this info online or in print. That's how I am reading your comments now.  I made the "tea" by just boiling persimmon strips without ginger and cinnamon, works also. I made it for a friend with a hiatal hernia caused by rheumatoid arthritis, and after 2 weeks on oral and infusion therapy of antibiotics, he threw up acid every time he ate because he had to stop Omeprazole/Prilosec because of Plavix interaction.</p>

<p>Scroll down and find Heartburn on the left side of the screen and click on it.</p>
        </div>
